article.description: — Tray Hollowell and Storm Murphy scored 19 points apiece as Wofford routed Toccoa Falls 88-49 on Wednesday night in a season opener.
article.headline: Hollowell, Murphy lead Wofford past Toccoa Falls 88-49
article.linkText: Hollowell, Murphy lead Wofford past Toccoa Falls 88-49
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- — Tray Hollowell and Storm Murphy scored 19 points apiece as Wofford routed Toccoa Falls 88-49 on Wednesday night in a season opener. Messiah Jones added 12 points and 12 rebounds for the Terriers, while Sam Godwin and Morgan Safford each had 10. Godwin grabbed seven rebounds. Wofford had a 13-10 lead five minutes into the game before taking off to a 49-15 halftime bulge. Alex Forde had 13 points for the Eagles. Luke Baham added 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
